History.The Spellplague:
{{fq
|text = We are priests of ''nothing!'' We feign wisdom and insight, and deceive ourselves into seeing ultimate truth in the lines of a painting or the curves of a sculpture.
|source=Menlidus
|width=220px
}}
During the Spellplague in [[1385 DR]], he and four companions ventured out to the [[Snowflake Mountains]] from Spirit Soaring. He found that his magic backfired, and caused the death of a friend. Only he and a single other returned alive. Menlidus was injured and caked in blood, whilst his companion, [[Dahlania]], had lost a leg, and was soon to be completely legless through amputation.
